<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-01-20T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-01-20T12:00:00-05:00" n="673" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d673">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.61/786: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-01-20T20:00:00+03:00">January
                                    20, 1941—8 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 10:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>116. In the course of a conversation Saturday night<note n="76" xml:id="d673fn76">January 18.</note> with Mikoyan,<note n="77" xml:id="d673fn77">Anastas Ivanovich Mikoyan, People’s Commissar for
                                Foreign Trade of the Soviet Union.</note> he expressed his
                            disappointment in a good-natured manner with the failure of the
                            conversations in Washington to make further progress than they had,
                            citing as an example that “only 42% of the machine tools purchased and
                            paid for by the Soviet Union in the United States had thus far been
                            released.”</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>